  "texts": [
    "Then, the next step is to continue to get clean data by post-editing translation output from that engine.",
    "This is a very important conclusion for \"low resource languages\".",
    "(2) Automated metrics deliver an illusion of measurementthey are a good tool for iterative stochastic gradient descent during training, but they do not measure quality (only some sort of similarity), are not compatible when any of the underlying factors change, provide results on a non-uniform scale even on their interval of validity, in general are not sufficiently reliable, and may be misleading.",
    "We can't rely on automatic metrics alone.",
    "Instead, human translation quality validation is a must and such validation can deny and reverse the results of automatic measurement."
  ],
